{
  "texts": [
    "In this case, UMAP (Uniform Manifold Approximation and Projection for Dimension Reduction, (McInnes & Healy, 2018) is currently the method of choice, as it preserves both the local and global structure of embeddings quite well.",
    "Section 9.4 presents an application of UMAP.",
    "As seen in Section 7, predicting the number of vehicles from the case descriptions is a relatively easy task for the transformer model, even in a multilingual situation.",
    "Therefore, we turn to a more challenging problem, presented in Case Study 3. focusing on those examples where the probability assigned to the false prediction was high, i.e.",
    "cases where the model was confident but wrong."
  ]
}